{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:23:02.189Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deep Learning (DL)"},{"type":"text","text":" is a specialized subset of machine learning that uses artificial neural networks with many layers to learn complex patterns from data, especially unstructured data like images, speech, and text."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key idea:"},{"type":"text","text":" DL is “machine learning with deep neural networks” — the “deep” refers to the many layers in the network."}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"DL in the hierarchy: AI → ML → DL → Gen AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deep Learning sits inside ML, which is inside AI:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"AI (Artificial Intelligence)\n └── ML (Machine Learning)\n      └── DL (Deep Learning)\n           └── Gen AI (Generative AI, often built on DL models)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI"},{"type":"text","text":": Any system that mimics human intelligence (rules, search, planning, ML, etc.)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ML"},{"type":"text","text":": AI that learns patterns from data using statistical algorithms"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"DL"},{"type":"text","text":": ML that uses "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deep neural networks"},{"type":"text","text":" with multiple layers to learn hierarchical representations"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gen AI"},{"type":"text","text":": AI that creates new content (text, images, code), typically using deep learning models like transformers"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Deep Learning works: neural networks and layers"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DL is built on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"artificial neural networks"},{"type":"text","text":" inspired by the human brain:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A neural network has "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"layers of nodes (“neurons”)"},{"type":"text","text":" connected by weighted edges"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Deep”"},{"type":"text","text":" means many layers (often 10s to 100s+) that process data in a hierarchy:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Early layers learn simple patterns (edges, tones, basic shapes) - Middle layers learn more complex patterns (parts of objects, syllables) - Late layers learn abstract concepts (faces, words, objects)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"nested hierarchy of concepts"},{"type":"text","text":" allows DL to handle tasks that are extremely hard for classical ML, such as:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Face recognition (Face ID)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-driving car perception"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Speech recognition (“Hey Google”)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Language translation"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"DL’s popularity exploded around "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2012"},{"type":"text","text":" after "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AlexNet"},{"type":"text","text":" dramatically won an image recognition challenge, enabled by:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Massive datasets from the internet"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful GPUs (from gaming)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Improved training algorithms"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Classical Machine Learning vs. Deep Learning"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Even within ML, there are two major approaches: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"classical ML"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deep learning"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Classical Machine Learning"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deep Learning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"ty